@startuml
title Widget Event Propagation

skinparam ParticipantPadding 8

participant "Frame/Mouse/Keyboard Module" as Module
participant "Root Widget" as Root
participant "Child Widget" as Child
participant "Leaf Widget" as Leaf
participant "EventView<T>" as Event

Module -> Root : dispatch*Event(record, optional device)
Root -> Event : create typed EventView
Root -> Root : _propagate(event, handler)

alt root inactive or event already consumed
	Root --> Module : stop
else active
	Root -> Child : _propagate(event, handler)
	alt child inactive
		Child --> Root : skip child subtree
	else child active
		Child -> Leaf : _propagate(event, handler)
		Leaf -> Leaf : _on*Event(event)
		alt leaf consumes
			Leaf -> Event : consume()
			Leaf --> Child : consumed
			Child --> Root : consumed
			Root --> Module : consumed
		else not consumed
			Leaf --> Child
			Child -> Child : _on*Event(event)
			Child --> Root
			Root -> Root : _on*Event(event)
		end
	end
end

note right of Event
EventView owns the consumed flag for this
dispatch only. Record data and device state
are exposed through const views.
end note

note over Root
Propagation is child-first. A consumed event
stops traversal before parent handlers that
have not yet run.
end note

@enduml
